N2  - This article discusses the award received by two papers that were published in ?Academy of Management Review? (AMR). The 2005 Best Article Award went to ?Economics Language and Assumptions: How Theories Can Become Self-Fulfilling,? by professors Ferraro, Pfeffer, and Sutton. The AMR Frame-Breaking, Innovative Theory Awards were given to one paper from each decade which contained the most innovative, frame-breaking theory development. The papers were chosen by a committee headed by Madan Pillutla.
AB  - This article discusses the award received by two papers that were published in ?Academy of Management Review? (AMR). The 2005 Best Article Award went to ?Economics Language and Assumptions: How Theories Can Become Self-Fulfilling,? by professors Ferraro, Pfeffer, and Sutton. The AMR Frame-Breaking, Innovative Theory Awards were given to one paper from each decade which contained the most innovative, frame-breaking theory development. The papers were chosen by a committee headed by Madan Pillutla.
