TY  - JOUR
T1  - Nice Try, Bill, But … There You Go Again
AU  - Van De Ven, Andrew H.
AU  - Johnson, Paul E.
Y1  - 2006/10/01
PY  - 2006
DA  - 2006/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2006.22527455
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2006.22527455
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 830
EP  - 832
VL  - 31
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Bill McKelvey's commentary is provocative, but four points need correction. (1) The purpose of engaged scholarship is not just to advance practice but to create scientific knowledge. (2) Bill's food chain metaphor mistakenly views the gap between science and practice as a knowledge transfer problem. (3) Bill ignores the impact of biases of researchers by only focusing on practitioner bias. (4) He considers differing views of researchers and practitioners as antithetical; we view them as complementary.
AB  - Bill McKelvey's commentary is provocative, but four points need correction. (1) The purpose of engaged scholarship is not just to advance practice but to create scientific knowledge. (2) Bill's food chain metaphor mistakenly views the gap between science and practice as a knowledge transfer problem. (3) Bill ignores the impact of biases of researchers by only focusing on practitioner bias. (4) He considers differing views of researchers and practitioners as antithetical; we view them as complementary.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2006.22527455
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2006.22527455
Y2  - 2026/04/24
